        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: consolidate security audit UI",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nReworks the artifact security surface around a single Security audit experience.\n\nThe root skill/plugin page now shows security status in the right-hand metadata sidebar, with the compact meter/verdict treatment and an info tooltip for the shared audit scope. The full audit page lives at `/<owner>/<skill>/security-audit` and `/plugins/<name>/security-audit`, with legacy scanner-specific security routes redirecting into the new combined page.\n\nThe full audit page combines overview, publisher note, static analysis, VirusTotal, and risk analysis sections. Static/VirusTotal pending states now stay visibly pending instead of reading as clean/no findings, and CodeQL targeted frontend security paths were updated to cover the new audit components and routes.\n\nAlso removes the old scanner page UI, removes the publisher-note info affordance, adjusts install prompt wrapping/segmented control sizing, and updates route/tests/spec notes for the new audit URL.\n\n## Tests\n\n- `bun run ci:static`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview`\n- `VITE_CONVEX_URL=https://example.invalid bun run test -- src/components/SkillSecurityScanResults.test.tsx src/components/DetailSecuritySummary.test.tsx src/__tests__/skill-security-scanner-route.test.tsx`\n- `bunx oxfmt --check src/components/SecurityAuditPage.tsx src/components/SkillSecurityScanResults.test.tsx .github/codeql/codeql-frontend-publish-security.yml`\n- Final autoreview: `autoreview clean: no accepted/actionable findings reported`\n",
